# Todo / tracker file placement

## Where files go

- **New** engineering trackers, subsystem checklists, and `*ToDo.md` / `*_ToDo/TODO.md` files belong under **`ToDo/`** at the repo root — not loose at repo root.
- **Main backlog:** `ToDo/TODO.md` (index of systems + cross-links to focused trackers).
- **Deferred product ideas:** `NEXTVERSION.md` stays at repo root (`next-version-capture.mdc`).

## Naming

- Subsystem trackers: `SomethingToDo.md` or `Something&AreaToDo.md` (match existing style).
- Add a one-line entry to `ToDo/README.md` when introducing a new tracker file.

## Cross-links

- From code comments, `README.md`, `AGENTS.md`, or other repo-root docs: use the full path, e.g. `ToDo/ToDo/TrainingGazeboSimulationToDo.md`.
- From another file **inside** `ToDo/`: same-folder links may use the basename only (`ToDo/TrainingGazeboSimulationToDo.md`).

## Hygiene

When a tracker item is **done**, follow `todo-list-hygiene.mdc` (migrate retained locks to `README_FULL.md`, delete the bullet — do not leave `[x]` closures in tracker files).
